cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as inflection generation and lemmatization. It also uses neural networks for string transduction, which is a common technique in NLP. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it employs imitation learning, a type of supervised learning, to train the model. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with developing an AI model for language tasks. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category as the paper uses neural networks for training the model. 

Finally, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the biases in Maximum Likelihood Estimation (MLE) training and proposes a new approach to address them.
